<p class="">    <h2>Key Challenges in the Commercial Display Refrigerator Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Energy Efficiency Regulations:</strong>            With growing environmental concerns, manufacturers face increasing pressure to comply with stringent energy efficiency standards. The need for innovation to reduce energy consumption can elevate production costs and complicate design processes.        </li>        <li>            <strong>High Initial Investment:</strong>            The upfront costs for advanced display refrigeration systems can be a significant barrier for small and medium-sized enterprises. This financial hurdle may limit market access and slow down the adoption of new, energy-efficient technologies.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Market Saturation:</strong>            In many regions, the market for commercial display refrigerators is becoming saturated. This saturation leads to heightened competition, forcing companies to engage in price wars that can adversely affect profit margins.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Maintaining Product Quality:</strong>            Ensuring the quality and safety of perishable goods requires effective temperature control and display. Any failure in these systems can lead to product spoilage, resulting in losses for retailers and decreased customer satisfaction.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Supply Chain Disruptions:</strong>            Global supply chain issues, including material shortages and transportation delays, pose ongoing challenges in sourcing components and delivering finished products. These disruptions can hinder manufacturers' ability to meet customer demand promptly.        </li>    </ul>    <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Commercial Display Refrigerator Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Smart Technology Integration:</strong>            The rise of IoT (Internet of Things) and smart technologies presents signifi